        "cooked": "<p>Spoofing is one side of this, which TLS does indeed prevent.  There\u2019s also a question of if a certificate is issued to one host, can it be moved and successfully reused by any other host.  There was a previous question about this <a href=\"https://forums.foundationdb.org/t/tls-plugin-automatic-hostname-ip-verification/1314\" class=\"inline-onebox\">TLS Plugin Automatic Hostname / IP Verification</a> , and nothing has changed since afaik.</p>",
